9 An Act relating to 2-1-1 services; amending 56 O.S.
2021, Section 3021, which relates to the Oklahoma 2-
10 1-1 Collaborative; removing obsolete language;
specifying certain services of 2-1-1 call centers;
11 placing the Collaborative under the administrative
oversight of the Department of Human Services;
12 modifying and removing certain powers and duties;
modifying membership of the Collaborative; specifying
13 procedures for appointment, reappointment, removal,
and vacancy of members; creating certain exclusion
14 for specified contracts; and providing an effective
date.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 56 O.S. 2021, Section 3021, is
19 amended to read as follows:
20 Section 3021. A. Beginning on January 1, 2011, the Oklahoma 2-
21 1-1 Advisory Collaborative shall be renamed the 2-1-1 Oklahoma
22 Coordinating Council. Beginning on July 1, 2021, the 2-1-1 Oklahoma
23 Coordinating Council shall be renamed the Oklahoma 2-1-1
24 Collaborative. The Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative is hereby
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4095 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 desi gnated as the state lead entity of all 2-1-1 call centers in
2 this state that are providing hotline services that include, but are
3 not limited to, support for food, housing, clothing, transportation,
4 and medical needs.
5 B. The Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative, under the administrative
6 oversight of the Department of Human Services, shall have the
7 following duties and responsibilities:
8 1. Develop and maintain a statewide coordinated approach for
9 the promotion of a 2-1-1 system;
10 2. Develop and maintain an integrated statewide 2-1-1 service
11 that avoids overlap of 2-1-1 call centers in the state;
12 3. Certify Register information and referral providers who wish
13 to become 2-1-1 call centers;
14 4. Develop and maintain certification Implement standards for
15 providers that operate as a 2-1-1 call center in the state in
16 compliance with the Alliance for Information and Referral Systems
17 accordance with national accreditation standards of Inform USA or
18 its successor entity;
19 5. Assure that each 2-1-1 call center is accountable and
20 maintains compliance with Corporation Commission standards;
21 6. Develop and maintain a process for 2-1-1 call center
22 accountability and compliance with state and national standards for
23 any contractual obligations;
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4095 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 7. Provide leadership and coordination for 2-1-1 call centers
2 as it relates to large-scale emergencies and homeland security
3 needs;
4 8. 7. Develop and implement a statewide, outcome-driven
5 strategic plan for 2-1-1 Oklahoma;
6 9. 8. Advocate for funding to support and sustain 2-1-1 system
7 delivery;
8 10. 9. Coordinate with national, state and local partners in
9 the provision of 2-1-1 services;
10 11. 10. Collaborate with such entities as may be required and
11 to the extent required under federal law or to receive federal
12 funding;
13 12. 11. Provide funding formula recommendations to the
14 administering entity responsible Department of Human Services for
15 the allocation of direct state and federal funds appropriated for 2-
16 1-1 Oklahoma, not including funds related to any contract described
17 under subsection E of this section; and
18 13. 12. Submit an annual report no later than September 1 of
19 each year to the cabinet Secretary for the cabinet area consisting
20 of the Department of Human Services, of the services rendered in the
21 past fiscal year by the 2-1-1 system. The report may also include
22 recommendations of the Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative.
23 C. 1. The membership of the Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative shall
24 be comprised of fifteen (15) nine (9) members, five of whom shall be
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4095 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 publ ic sector representatives and ten of whom shall be private
2 sector representatives. The initial members shall be selected by
3 the current 2-1-1 call centers in this state as of the effective
4 date of this act. Vacancies that occur after the selection of the
5 initial members shall be filled by the Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative
6 as follows:
7 a. the Director of Human Services or designee,
8 b. the Director of the Oklahoma Department of Emergency
9 Management or designee,
10 c. the State Commissioner of Health or designee, and
11 d. six private sector representatives. The Governor, the
12 President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and the Speaker
13 of the House of Representatives shall each appoint one
14 such member who resides in the 2-1-1 service area for
15 western Oklahoma and one such member who resides in
16 the 2-1-1 service area for eastern Oklahoma.
17 2. The initial appointments of the private sector
18 representatives described in subparagraph d of paragraph 1 of this
19 subsection shall be made as follows:
20 a. the Governor shall appoint two members to serve
21 initial terms of one (1) year each,
22 b. the President Pro Tempore of the Senate shall appoint
23 one member to serve an initial term of two (2) years
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4095 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 and one member to serve an initial term of three (3)
2 years, and
3 c. the Speaker of the House of Representatives shall
4 appoint one member to serve an initial term of two (2)
5 years and one member to serve an initial term of three
6 (3) years.
7 Thereafter, such members shall serve terms of three (3) years and
8 may be reappointed. Such members may be removed by their appointing
9 authorities for cause. Any vacancy shall be filled by the
10 appointing authority for the remainder of the unexpired term.
11 3. The Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative shall meet not less than
12 two times per year for the purpose of reviewing and carrying out its
13 duties and responsibilities.
14 3. 4. The members of the Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative shall
15 adopt by-laws governing its operations including terms of office,
16 the conduct of meetings and such other functions as the Oklahoma 2-
17 1-1 Collaborative deems necessary to carry out its duties and
18 responsibilities.
19 4. 5. Members shall serve without compensation or reimbursement
20 for expenses; provided, that members who are public officers may be
21 reimbursed for necessary expenses as provided by law.
22 D. If federal funding related to 2-1-1 services becomes
23 available to the state, the state may comply with any requirements
24 necessary to make application for and receive such federal funding.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4095 SFLR Page 5
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 E. The Oklahoma 2-1-1 Collaborative shall not have jurisdiction
2 over any statewide contract or competitively bid contract awarded to
3 an entity that operates a 2-1-1 call center if the contract does not
4 relate to 2-1-1 services, and nothing in this section shall be
5 construed to otherwise apply to any such contract.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
